description.narrative: (Nigeria): The Monitoring, Evaluation and Learning (MEL) Activity provides cross-sectoral, Mission-wide support on project and activity level monitoring, evaluation, and learning. The goal of this activity is to help transform USAID/Nigeria into a premier practitioner of program monitoring and evaluation rooted in organizational learning and adaptation. The MEL Activity provides continuous, on-the-ground, on-demand and systematic support to all USAID/Nigeria technical teams, sectors, and implementing partners on performance monitoring, data verification, performance and impact evaluations, project- and activity-level monitoring, evaluation and learning plans, organizational learning, capacity building and knowledge management. ..Due to security restrictions for USAID/Nigeria staff, the MEL Activity supports third-party, field-based monitoring to augment the Mission's activity monitoring efforts. The MEL Activity is also designed to support enhanced accountability and engagement with non-USAID stakeholders so that USAID can benefit from their perspectives through shared learning and problem solving that improves Mission results and achievement..
